# Getting Started with PyShield-SMR

PyShield-SMR is a comprehensive radiation shielding analysis framework designed to demonstrate radiation physics and nuclear engineering principles for Small Modular Reactors.

## Quick Start (5 minutes)

### Installation

```bash
# Clone or navigate to the project directory
cd pyshield-smr

# Install in development mode (includes test dependencies)
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Verify installation
python -m pyshield_smr.cli.main --help
```

### Run Your First Analysis

```bash
# Execute the simplest example: Co-60 behind 5 cm lead
python -m pyshield_smr.cli.main run examples/01_point_kernel_shielding/config.yaml

# Output will be written to: reports/TIMESTAMP_CASENAME/
# - report.md (human-readable summary)
# - report.html (styled HTML)
# - qa_manifest.json (governance metadata)
```

### View Results

```bash
# Open the report in your browser
open reports/*/report.html

# Or read the Markdown version
cat reports/*/report.md
```

